description: Artificial Intelligence (AI) is becoming a creative force both within and outside gallery walls. But legal uncertainties could hinder the hype. The latest in a CNA series on AI in Southeast Asia looks at how the technology is redesigning artistic practices, and what lies ahead.
title: AI in Southeast Asia: Muse or menace? How artists in the region are grappling with new technologies

description: Female inmates working at a call centre in Changi Prison gain confidence and skills to re-enter the world outside, in this final part of a CNA series about life in jail.
title: Behind Bars: Who picks up when you call customer service? It could be a prison inmate

description: Singaporeans have become unhappier over the past few years, despite rising median household income levels. NUS Business School’s Siok Kuan Tambyah and Yuen Wei Lun explore why this is so.
title: Commentary: Can money buy happiness? It’s a complex question in Singapore

description: Something as simple as rubbing our eyes can introduce pathogens leading to infection, blindness and, in the worst case, death, says a Lancaster University professor.
title: Commentary: Eye infections might seem like a minor complaint - but they can cause blindness and even death

description: Israel’s use of an AI-enabled targeting system in Gaza has fed the debate about military technology, says the Financial Times’ John Thornhill.
title: Commentary: War by algorithm raises new moral dangers

description: As travellers flock to the island possibly in record numbers this year, the programme Insight explores what lies behind the locals’ love-hate relationship with tourism and what can be done to stem the feelings of discontent.
title: Faced with overtourism, is Bali becoming a paradise lost?

description: A tearoom, sunken courtyards, silk wallpaper and an eight-metre-long timber carving made by 40 artisans are some highlights in this traditional courtyard house.
title: How this traditional courtyard house in Beijing transformed into a luxurious private clubhouse
